cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of deep neural networks on spiking neuromorphic computing systems.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of memristor-based SNC systems, which are an emerging technology.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of DNNs on a specific hardware architecture.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision tasks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency gains achieved by implementing DNNs on a specific system.
